    public final class PrefixSha256Condition
extends CompoundSha256Condition
implements CompoundCondition
    Implementation of a crypto condition based on a prefix, a sub-condition and the SHA-256 function.

      • PrefixSha256Condition

        public PrefixSha256Condition(byte[] prefix,
                             long maxMessageLength,
                             Condition subcondition)
        Constructs an instance of the condition.
        パラメータ:
        prefix - The prefix to use when creating the fingerprint.
        maxMessageLength - The maximum length of the message.
        subcondition - A condition on which this condition depends.

      • PrefixSha256Condition

        public PrefixSha256Condition(long cost,
                             byte[] fingerprint,
                             EnumSet<CryptoConditionType> subtypes)

        Constructs an instance of the condition.

        This constructor _should_ be primarily used by Codecs, whereas developers should, in general, use the PrefixSha256Condition(byte[], long, Condition) constructor, or else create an actual fulfillment via PrefixSha256Fulfillment.PrefixSha256Fulfillment(byte[], long, Fulfillment) and then generate a condition from that object.

        パラメータ:
        cost - The cost of this condition.
        fingerprint - The calculated fingerprint.
        subtypes - A set of condition rsa for the conditions that this one depends on.
